org.ejbca.core.protocol.ws.client.gen

Class HardTokenDataWS

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.ejbca.core.protocol.ws.client.gen.HardTokenDataWS

  • public class HardTokenDataWS
extends java.lang.Object
    Value object containing WS representation of a hard token data it contains information about PIN/PUK codes, hardtoken serial number certificate stored on the card.
    Author:
    Philip Vendil $Id: HardTokenDataWS.java 21645 2015-07-31 13:25:43Z mikekushner $

      • HardTokenDataWS

        public HardTokenDataWS(int tokenType,
               java.lang.String label,
               java.lang.String hardTokenSN,
               java.lang.String copyOfSN,
               java.util.List<PinDataWS> pinDatas,
               boolean encKeyKeyRecoverable)
        Constuctor that should be used with the genTokenCertificates request
        Parameters:
        tokenType - one of the TOKENTYPE_ constants
        label - indicating the use of the token, one of the LABEL_ constants
        hardTokenSN - the SN of the hard token
        copyOfSN - of this is a copy of another hard token, specify its SN otherwise use null.
        pinDatas - a List of pin datas with PIN and PUK
        encKeyKeyRecoverable - if the token have a special encryption key it should be specified if it is recoverable or not.

      • HardTokenDataWS

        public HardTokenDataWS(int tokenType,
               java.lang.String label,
               java.lang.String hardTokenSN,
               java.lang.String copyOfSN,
               java.util.List<java.lang.String> copies,
               java.util.List<PinDataWS> pinDatas,
               java.util.List<Certificate> certificates,
               boolean encKeyKeyRecoverable)
        Constuctor of a HardTokenDataWS with all it fields. This constructor should be used on the server side of EJBCA
        Parameters:
        tokenType - one of the TOKENTYPE_ constants
        label - indicating the use of the token, one of the LABEL_ constants
        hardTokenSN - the SN of the hard token
        copyOfSN - of this is a copy of another hard token, specify its SN otherwise use null.
        copies - if there is copies of this hard token a list of serial number is specified.
        pinDatas - a List of pin datas with PIN and PUK
        certificates - the certificate stored on the token
        encKeyKeyRecoverable - if the token have a special encryption key it should be specified if it is recoverable or not.
